The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, December 18, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Dec. 17: The CID has arrested Ranjan Ghosh, 34, from Mumbai on the charge of mentally harassing his wife of seven months and forcing her to leave him. 

 According to the complaint lodged by the womans father, Ranjan Ghosh ? who hails from Thakurpukur and works in Mumbai ? has married four times in the past two-and-a-half years and was planning his fifth. 

 Calcutta: Two persons were seriously injured in separate road accidents on Friday. Around 11.55 am, Shila Mondal, 45, was crossing Broad Street when a bus knocked her down. She was wounded in the head and was admitted to a nursing home. Barely an hour later, nine-year-old Sayan Roychowdhury was hit by a motorcycle on Duff Street. 

 Calcutta: The Government Railway Police on Saturday caught a man boarding the Mumbai-bound Gitanjali Express with a fake ticket. Bishnu Mandal, a 22-year-old daily-wage earner, was arrested from the new complex of Howrah station.

 Calcutta: A fire broke out in two offices on the third floor of Marshall House on Netaji Subhas Road on Saturday, destroying important papers and equipment, including photo-copiers, fax machines and computers. No one was injured.

 Calcutta: An unidentified man called the office of an insurance company at Church Lane under Hare police station to say explosives had been planted there. But it turned out to be a hoax.




